Ivory Coast youngsters Hamed and Amad Traore are attracting interest from Arsenal. Hamed is currently on a two-year loan at Sassuolo from Empoli and he has returned three goals in 20 league appearances while Amad broke into Atalanta’s first-team this campaign and scored a goal on his Serie Adebut against Udinese in October. READ ALSO: Mikel Obi in talks with Brazilian club Botafogo The Ivorians are currently enjoying their development in Italy and might be difficult for the Gunners to prize away, with Juventus the latest side to be turned down in their attempt to sign 20-year-old Hamed.